      <div class="card-hl">Defence stocks surged ~6% on FY27 Day 1 — Trump's NATO exit hint plus Rajnath's ₹2.38 lakh crore defence deal clearance landed simultaneously</div>
      <div class="card-deck">The Nifty India Defence Index rising nearly 6% in a single session is not a normal event. Two catalysts converged on the same day. First, Trump's statement that pulling out of NATO is "beyond reconsideration" is a structural re-rating event for global defence spending. If the US security umbrella over Europe shrinks, European nations need to ramp up domestic defence manufacturing immediately. That demand spills over to allies and suppliers globally, and India's defence export ambitions suddenly have a much larger addressable market. Second, Defence Minister Rajnath Singh cleared procurement proposals worth ₹2.38 lakh crore in a single DAC (Defence Acquisition Council) meeting — one of the largest single-day defence clearances in India's history. The combination of a structural global demand expansion and a massive domestic order signal sent investors rushing into HAL, BEL, Bharat Dynamics, Mazagon Dock, and BEML. Source: Aftermarket Report.</div>
